The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	London: Bell has been called up for the last two matches of the troubled series against Pakistan after scoring 107 off 95 balls in Warwickshires victory over Somerset at Lords.The 28-year-old was not involved earlier as he had just returned from a metatarsal injury but is deemed a guaranteed pick for Thursdays Ashes squad announcement.         
	Melbourne: Former Australian spinner Shane Warne is reportedly foraying into the nightclub industry along with football player Dermott Brereton in Melbourne, Sydney and India.        
	Milan: Inter Milan captain Javier Zanetti was taken to hospital following Sundays 2-1 win at Palermo after complaining of chest pains. He was taken to the hospital at the doctors suggestion. However, the 37-year-old assured his fans that he was fine after the hospital visit.        
	London: Liverpool co-owner Tom Hicks is reported to have told the clubs board that he will sign a 281million refinancing deal to stay in charge at Anfield on Oct 1. The American, who met Liverpool chairman Martin Broughton in London for talks last week, hopes the deal with the Blackstone/GSO Group will allow him another two years to find a buyer for the Merseyside club.         
	Atzenbrugg: An erratic four-over 76 in the third round saw Indian golfer Shiv Kapur slip to the tied 61st spot in the Austrian Open here. Kapurs overall total stood at three-over 218 after the penultimate round.        
	Khanty Mansiysk: In the absence of Viswanathan Anand, Krishnan Sasikiran will be Indias best bet in the Chess Olympiad that starts here Monday.        
	Sydney: Former world No. 1 Lleyton Hewitt may be sidelined for up to three weeks after sustaining a right hand injury that forced him to pull out of Australias Davis Cup World Group playoff against Belgium.                                                                                                                                                      
